"appPurposeContent": "This app is designed to help people with celiac disease or gluten intolerance by providing a secure e-commerce platform, adapted recipes, educational games, and resources to maintain a safe gluten-free lifestyle.",
  "featuresTitle": "Key Features",
  "feature1": "🛒 **Gluten-Free Online Store** - Shop with confidence for certified gluten-free products with direct delivery.",
  "feature2": "🎮 **Educational Mini-Games** - Learn to identify safe foods in a fun way with our interactive games.",
  "feature3": "🍽 **Gluten-Free Recipes** - Discover delicious and safe meal ideas created by nutrition experts.",
  "feature4": "📍 **Local Business Directory** - Find certified gluten-free grocery stores and restaurants near you.",
  "contactUsTitle": "Contact Us",
  "contactEmail": "gluttex.team@gmail.com",
  "contactPhone": "+213-XXX-XXX-XXX",
  "illnessOverviewContent": "Celiac disease is an autoimmune disorder where gluten ingestion damages the small intestine. It can cause digestive problems, nutritional deficiencies, and other complications. Strict lifelong gluten avoidance is the only effective treatment.",
  "symptom1": "💨 **Digestive Issues** - Bloating, diarrhea, constipation, nausea and vomiting.",
  "symptom2": "⚡ **Chronic Fatigue** - Caused by malabsorption of essential nutrients.",
  "symptom3": "🦴 **Bone Complications** - Increased risk of osteoporosis due to poor calcium and vitamin D absorption.",
  "treatmentContent": "Treatment requires strict lifelong gluten-free diet. Patients must avoid wheat, barley, rye and their derivatives. Nutritional support and tools like Gluttex help prevent accidental exposure.",
  "resource1": "📖 **Celiac Disease Foundation** - [www.celiac.org](https://www.celiac.org)",
  "resource2": "📱 **Interactive Shopping Guide** - Built-in app feature to scan suspicious ingredient lists.",
  "resource3": "👩‍⚕️ **Specialist Directory** - Find gastroenterologists and nutritionists specializing in celiac disease near you.",
  
